'''Dame Olga Patricia Symmonds''', [[Order of Barbados|GCM]], [[Order of the British Empire|DBE]] (born 18 October 1925), best known as '''Patricia Symmonds''', is a [[Barbados|Barbadian]] politician, member of the [[Senate of Barbados]] and a former teacher.

The only daughter of Algernon French Symmonds and his wife, Olga (née Harper), she is the elder sister of [[Barbados|Barbadian]] diplomat, Algernon Washington Symmonds. She was educated at [[Queen's College (Barbados)|Queen's College, Barbados]], and travelled to the [[United Kingdom]] to study at the [[University of Reading]] and the [[Institute of Education]]. {{citation needed|date=October 2014}}

As a teacher from 1945–85, she was Deputy Principal of the [[The St. Michael School|St. Michael School, Saint Michael, Barbados]] from 1963–76, then Principal of the school from 1976-85. She was a part-time lecturer and tutor at [[Cave Hill, Saint Michael, Barbados|Cave Hill Campus]] from 1963-65. {{citation needed|date=October 2014}}

Since 1994, she has been a Senator of Barbados and was a member of the [[Privy Council]] of Barbados from 1997 to 2000. She was created a [[Order of the British Empire|Dame Commander of the Order of the British Empire]] in 2000. {{citation needed|date=October 2014}}

